1
00:00:06,600 --> 00:00:09,060
美国空军和海军
Air and naval forces of the United States

2
00:00:09,060 --> 00:00:12,150
对恐怖组织设施进行了一系列的打击行动
launched a series of strikes against terrorist facilities...

3
00:00:12,150 --> 00:00:14,590
泛美航空103号航班坠毁于洛克比镇
Pan Am flight 103 crashed into the town of Lockerbie.

4
00:00:14,590 --> 00:00:17,890
他在非洲 欧洲和中东都制裁过恐怖行动
He has sanctioned acts of terror in Africa, Europe and the Middle East.

5
00:00:17,890 --> 00:00:20,940
针对科威特的侵略是不会长久的
This will not stand, this aggression against, uh, Kuwait.

6
00:00:20,940 --> 00:00:22,610
这种对恐怖主义赤裸裸的追求 
This relentless pursuit of terror.

7
00:00:22,610 --> 00:00:23,920
我们会一视同仁
We will make no distinction...

8
00:00:23,920 --> 00:00:26,720
科尔号驱逐舰在亚丁港加油时遭到袭击
The USS Cole was attacked while refueling in the port of Aden.

9
00:00:26,720 --> 00:00:28,270
这是一次恐怖袭击
This was an act of terrorism.

10
00:00:28,950 --> 00:00:31,570
是卑鄙而软弱的行径
It was a despicable and cowardly act.

11
00:00:31,570 --> 00:00:35,480
我们为您带来的下一首桑巴是一首怀旧金曲
The next samba we're going to swing for you is one of the good old favorites.

12
00:00:35,480 --> 00:00:37,980
直到他被阻止
...until something stops him.

13
00:00:37,980 --> 00:00:41,390
就在我的眼前 我完全没有料到会处这种事
It was right in front of my eyes, and I never saw it coming.

14
00:00:42,230 --> 00:00:44,900
那飞机直冲着世贸大楼撞了过去
That plane crashed into the World Trade Center.

15
00:00:46,310 --> 00:00:47,810
上千的民众在逃命
Thousands of people running.

16
00:00:47,810 --> 00:00:52,540
我们必须也会在国内外保持警惕
We must and we will remain vigilant at home and abroad.

17
00:00:57,570 --> 00:01:00,820
你是我认识的最聪明 也是最笨的人
You're the smartest and the dumbest fucking person I've ever known.

18
00:01:02,290 --> 00:01:03,470
弄错的人可不是我
I'm not the one who got it wrong.

19
00:01:03,470 --> 00:01:05,540
只有我做对了
I'm the only one who got it right.

20
00:01:09,810 --> 00:01:10,730
拿下他们
Take 'em.

21
00:01:11,750 --> 00:01:12,770
统统拿下
Take 'em all.

22
00:01:24,970 --> 00:01:28,230
前情提要
Previously on Homeland...

23
00:01:28,230 --> 00:01:29,840
我昨天和总统谈过了
I spoke to the President yesterday.

24
00:01:29,840 --> 00:01:33,770
他想要对情报工作做出一些调整
He's exploring some changes in intelligence practice.

25
00:01:33,770 --> 00:01:37,990
我不会为了让你支持我当局长
而改变自己的看法
I won't temper my views just to get your support for my confirmation as Director.

26
00:01:37,990 --> 00:01:40,620
被提名为局长的是我
I'm the one getting nominated as Director.

27
00:01:41,850 --> 00:01:44,800
现在这个局子一团乱
The Agency is being driven into the fucking ground.

28
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:48,650
我们希望你能成为你在参议院以及
专责委员会上所承诺的改革者
The hope is that you are the reformer your record in the Senate would indicate.

29
00:01:48,650 --> 00:01:52,180
那就是说你决定接受改革了?
So, then, you agree that change is in order?

30
00:01:52,180 --> 00:01:54,720
- 是的
- 那是Javadi吗?
Yes, I do. Is that Javadi?

31
00:01:54,720 --> 00:01:57,260
和我们的妻子在德黑兰的一家法式餐厅里
In a French restaurant in Tehran with their wives.

32
00:01:57,260 --> 00:02:00,590
我们当时是国王执政末期的年轻情报官
We were young intelligence officers during the dying days of the Shah.

33
00:02:00,590 --> 00:02:03,340
我眼看着一个我自以为了解的人变成野兽
I watched the man I thought I knew become an animal.

34
00:02:03,340 --> 00:02:05,500
所以这次行动是你的报复?
So this operation is your revenge?

35
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:09,540
我的报复是在四个月后帮助他的妻儿逃到美国
Revenge was when I helped his wife and son escape to the West four months later.

36
00:02:09,540 --> 00:02:13,140
我需要你去盯着Carrie
我们放她出去引伊朗人上钩
I need your eyes on Carrie. We dangled her to draw the Iranians out.

37
00:02:13,140 --> 00:02:16,870
- 正是Javadi本人
- Carrie Mathison
Javadi himself. Carrie Mathison.

38
00:02:16,870 --> 00:02:20,340
- 我们现在是不是独处?
- 没有人在监听
Are we completely alone now? No one is listening.

39
00:02:20,340 --> 00:02:22,590
我们来谈谈Nasser Hejazi吧
It's time we talk about Nasser Hejazi.

40
00:02:22,590 --> 00:02:26,500
你用他的名字从革命卫队那里
侵吞了超过四千五百万美元
Whose name you used to embezzle more than $45 million dollars.

41
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:31,120
- 你现在是你自己国家的敌人
- 那为什么我还没有被捕?
You are now an enemy of your own state. So why am I not arrested already?

42
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:34,450
- Saul想先和你谈谈
- 他会屈服的 对不对?
Saul would like to talk to you first. He will turn, won't he?

43
00:02:34,450 --> 00:02:37,260
让一个情报官员背叛自己的国家
Turning an intelligence officer against his own country.

44
00:02:39,370 --> 00:02:41,940
没有什么工作比这个更微妙且无法捉摸
Well, that's the most delicate and uncertain work there is.

45
00:02:41,940 --> 00:02:44,910
他不肯立刻跟我来 说不想惊动他的人
He wouldn't come with me right away. Said it wouldn't fly with his guys.

46
00:02:44,910 --> 00:02:47,670
太冒险了 所以我和他定了见面时间 
It was too risky. So I set a meet for later.

47
00:02:47,670 --> 00:02:49,500
原计划是直接带他来这里
Plan was to bring him straight here.

48
00:02:51,610 --> 00:02:52,650
需要帮助吗?
Can I help you?

49
00:03:01,870 --> 00:03:05,570
- 住手 不然我开枪了
- 现在我准备好去见Saul了
Stop or I shoot. Now I'm ready to see Saul.

50
00:03:06,350 --> 00:03:10,020
死了两个人 有很多血
这里他妈都血流成河了 Saul
There's two fatalities and a lot of blood. It's a fucking bloodbath, Saul.

51
00:03:10,020 --> 00:03:12,410
尽快把他带离那里 带上凶器
You got to get him out of there as fast as possible. And get the murder weapon.

52
00:03:12,410 --> 00:03:14,120
孩子要怎么办?
What do we do about the baby?

53
00:03:14,120 --> 00:03:16,230
别管他 你们不能留下踪迹
Leave it. You weren't there.

54
00:03:17,160 --> 00:03:20,710
你看起来不像是一个刚刚得到
自己职业生涯中最大资产的人
You don't look like a man who just landed the biggest asset of his career.

