梅子酒
Plum wine.

61
00:03:48,890 --> 00:03:51,690
是啊 伊朗产的一种酒
Yeah, some kind of Iranian thing.

62
00:03:51,690 --> 00:03:53,700
我还以为穆斯林不喝酒呢
I thought Muslims didn't drink.

63
00:03:59,250 --> 00:04:01,470
- 多少下?
- 什么?
How many? What? 

64
00:04:01,470 --> 00:04:02,890
他扎了她多少下?
He hit her how many times?

65
00:04:02,890 --> 00:04:07,070
粗略看来至少有十几下
I can see at least a dozen separate strikes.

66
00:04:07,070 --> 00:04:09,330
说实话 用这东西的话...谁数得清啊?
Honestly, though, with this... who the hell knows?

67
00:04:09,330 --> 00:04:13,000
- Cal?
- 我们还在找凶器呢 Cort
Cal? We're still looking for the murder weapons here, Cort.

68
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:17,680
我有更好的消息 邻居的监控摄像头拍到了这个
I may have something better. Neighbor's security camera picked it up.

69
00:04:23,280 --> 00:04:26,010
每月的第一个周五 德黑兰的阿斯卡利银行
Money is wired from the Al Askari Bank in Tehran

70
00:04:26,010 --> 00:04:30,450
就会把钱汇到卡拉卡斯西班牙拉丁商会的分会
the first Friday of every month to the HLBC subsidiary in Caracas.

71
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:35,250
这里有你的签名
On your signature there.

72
00:04:36,350 --> 00:04:40,050
我们顺着钱查下去 查到了一系列的恐怖行动
We have traced the funds downstream to a series of terrorist actions,

73
00:04:40,050 --> 00:04:42,070
包括对CIA的攻击
 including the attack on the CIA.

74
00:04:42,780 --> 00:04:50,010
但是钱也进了你自己的私人账户
你侵吞了革命卫队差不多五千万美元
But also to your personal accounts where you've diverted nearly $50 million of Revolutionary Guard money.

75
00:04:53,130 --> 00:04:56,640
如果伊斯兰革命卫队发现的话 你死罪难逃
That's punishable by death if the IRGC were to find out.

76
00:04:59,150 --> 00:05:00,690
你想说什么 Saul?
What's your point, Saul?

77
00:05:01,650 --> 00:05:03,740
被个丫头拉下了马?
That I've been brought down by a girl?

78
00:05:05,130 --> 00:05:07,470
被两个丫头?
By two girls?

79
00:05:20,980 --> 00:05:21,790
够了
Enough.

80
00:05:23,670 --> 00:05:25,640
我想他了解自己的处境
I think he appreciates the situation.

81
00:05:45,140 --> 00:05:48,430
- 他很会操纵人 他很擅长
- 我知道
He manipulates people. That's what he does. I know. 

82
00:05:48,430 --> 00:05:49,840
别让他得逞了
You can't let him get to you.

83
00:05:51,970 --> 00:05:53,120
他得逞了
Well, he does.

84
00:06:04,930 --> 00:06:06,370
你是在哪儿找到她的?
Where'd you find that one?

85
00:06:07,990 --> 00:06:10,880
满腔怒火的伊朗难民多着呢
The list of outraged Iranian exiles is long.

86
00:06:13,620 --> 00:06:15,010
她不会干很久的
She won't last.

87
00:06:15,010 --> 00:06:17,810
啊 1976年你就这么说过我
Well, that's what you said about me in 1976.

88
00:06:18,730 --> 00:06:20,450
那时我们才刚开始
When we were both starting out.

89
00:06:23,330 --> 00:06:24,670
所以你抓到我了
So you got me.

90
00:06:26,030 --> 00:06:28,090
你觉得自豪吗?
Are you proud of yourself?

91
00:06:28,090 --> 00:06:29,230
目前是
So far.

92
00:06:30,910 --> 00:06:32,320
我知道你要什么
I know what you want.

93
00:06:34,450 --> 00:06:35,310
是什么?
What's that?

94
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:38,170
让我把知道的都说出来
To clean me of what I know.

95
00:06:39,350 --> 00:06:43,310
我猜你一定很想知道我国核武器计划的进展 啊?
I imagine the state of our nuclear weapons program is high on your list, huh?

96
00:06:46,990 --> 00:06:49,140
你要和我做交易
There is a deal to be made.

97
00:06:49,140 --> 00:06:50,960
不然我早进监狱了
Or I'd be in prison by now.

98
00:06:55,980 --> 00:06:57,530
如果我开口...
If I talk...

99
00:06:57,530 --> 00:06:59,620
如果我那么做的话
if I do that,

100
00:06:59,620 --> 00:07:01,190
我需要保护
I need protection.

101
00:07:01,190 --> 00:07:05,310
给我在迈阿密找一个安全的房子 要带警卫
I need a secure compound in Miami with a guard detail.

102
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:09,000
然后把我的钱解冻
And I want my money unfrozen.

103
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,250
所有的钱
All of it.

104
00:07:13,150 --> 00:07:14,650
就这些?
Is that everything?

105
00:07:15,820 --> 00:07:16,770
目前就这些
For now.

106
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:20,130
所以你已经想过了?
So you've put some thought into this?

107
00:07:21,150 --> 00:07:22,620
这就是我的条件
Those are my terms.

108
00:07:25,310 --> 00:07:27,810
好
Okay.

109
00:07:29,420 --> 00:07:30,800
那是你的条件
Those are your terms.

110
00:07:34,010 --> 00:07:35,690
但是问题是你弄错了
But the problem is you got it all wrong.

111
00:07:36,810 --> 00:07:39,730
因为我想从你那儿得到的不只是情报
'Cause what I want from you is not just intelligence.

112
00:07:39,730 --> 00:07:43,600
你觉得我为什么要历尽千辛万苦
找出你的金融劣迹?
Why do you think I went through the trouble of documenting your financial misdeeds?

113
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:45,560
为什么?
Why?

114
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:47,880
你杀了219个美国人
You killed 219 Americans.

115
00:07:48,650 --> 00:07:51,780
你以为我在乎你侵吞革命卫队的钱啊?
Think I care you also ripped off the Revolutionary Guard?

116
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:56,430
我早给你定好了计划
I got plans for you.

117
00:07:56,430 --> 00:07:59,080
你透露一两个国家机密就想脱身是不可能的
Much bigger than you spilling a few state secrets.

118
00:08:00,360 --> 00:08:01,670
什么计划?
What plans?

119
00:08:01,670 --> 00:08:03,860
我要把你派回伊朗
I'm gonna play you back into Iran.

120
00:08:05,960 --> 00:08:07,690
从现在起 你为我们工作
From now on, you work for us.

121
00:08:09,410 --> 00:08:10,630
为我
For me.

122
00:08:11,700 --> 00:08:13,730
我是你的新情报官员
I'm your new case officer.

123
00:08:19,140 --> 00:08:20,340
行不通的
It won't work.

124
00:08:21,470 --> 00:08:23,740
- 为什么?
- 你让我暴露了
Why's that? You burned me back home.

125
00:08:23,740 --> 00:08:25,630
- 怎么说?
- 我和你见过面了
- How? - I'm here with you.

126
00:08:25,630 --> 00:08:27,540
- 他们可不知道
- 他们会知道的
- They don't know that. - Oh, they will.

127
00:08:27,540 --> 00:08:30,840
谁会告诉他们啊? 我不会 你不会
Who's going to tell them? Not me, not you.

128
00:08:30,840 --> 00:08:32,420
你自愿来到这里
You came here under your own steam.

129
00:08:32,420 --> 00:08:35,380
不管你是怎么进来的 你的故事还是说得通的
However you managed that, your story's still intact.

130
00:08:35,380 --> 00:08:36,810
如果我拒绝离开呢?
And if I refuse to go?

131
00:08:36,810 --> 00:08:37,870
明白了吗?
So we're clear?

132
00:08:37,870 --> 00:08:40,820
要么我送你回伊朗 要么就是另一条路
I'm sending you back to Tehran one way or the other.

133
00:08:40,820 --> 00:08:44,210
不当我的情报员就当革命的叛军吧
Either as my asset or a traitor to the Revolution.

134
00:08:44,210 --> 00:08:45,990
- 他一开始的计划就是这个?
- 嘘
- Was this always the plan? - Shh.

135
00:08:46,740 --> 00:08:48,320
别以为我不会 Majid
Don't think I won't, Majid.

136
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:51,850
那里可没有法庭 也不会让你一死了之
That's not a trial and quick execution you're facing there.

137
00:08:51,850 --> 00:08:53,580
首先你会受到折磨
You'll be tortured first.

138
00:08:53,580 --> 00:08:56,450
我也知道当众吊死现在又重新流行起来了
And I understand public hangings are back in vogue.

139
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:01,570
你想知道什么 我都说
I will tell you everything you want to know,

140
00:09:01,570 --> 00:09:05,060
我毫无保留地告诉你 但是我不能回去
chapter and verse, but I can't go back.

141
00:09:05,060 --> 00:09:07,020
- 你两件事都得做
- 不 我不做
You will do both. No, I won't.

142
00:09:07,020 --> 00:09:09,410
- 你必须得这么做 
- 我不做!
- Yes, you will. - No, I won't!

143
00:09:10,170 --> 00:09:11,440
你流血了
You're bleeding.

144
00:10:04,910 --> 00:10:06,340
下午好
Good afternoon.

145
00:10:06,340 --> 00:10:08,850
- 嗯
- 晚上过得很糟?
Yeah. Rough night?

146
00:10:08,850 --> 00:10:11,560
- 也没有
- 你看起来很累
Not especially. You look tired.

147
00:10:16,070 --> 00:10:17,210
想喝点什么吗?
Can I get you anything?

148
00:10:18,190 --> 00:10:20,260
你已经失踪很久了
You've been MIA for days now.

149
00:10:22,120 --> 00:10:23,060
不算是失踪吧
Not really.

150
00:10:23,060 --> 00:10:24,070
我在这里啊
I've been here.

151
00:10:25,680 --> 00:10:29,410
你旷工了 Saul也是
You've been absent. Saul, too.

152
00:10:29,410 --> 00:10:31,160
能不能解释一下?
You care to shed any light on that?

153
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:33,760
去和Saul谈吧
Talk to Saul.

154
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:38,260
我说过了 很难找到他的人
Like I said, he's not so easy to find.

155
00:10:43,100 --> 00:10:45,010
你是我的人 Peter
You're my guy, Peter.

156
00:10:45,010 --> 00:10:46,850
是我把你招进来 训练你的
I recruited you. I brought you up.

157
00:10:47,500 --> 00:10:51,530
- 你想说什么?
- 我想说的是我希望从你嘴里
- What's your point? - My point is that entitles me to a certain amount of forthrightness.

158
00:10:51,530 --> 00:10:52,590
听到实话
From you.

159
00:10:54,290 --> 00:10:56,870
Bethesda今早出了一起双重谋杀案
There was a double murder earlier today in Bethesda.

160
00:10:57,760 --> 00:11:02,170
Fariba Javadi 伊朗安全局副局长的前妻
Fariba Javadi, ex-wife of the Iranian Deputy Security Chief.

161
00:11:02,170 --> 00:11:03,680
还有她的儿媳
Also her daughter-in-law.

162
00:11:04,460 --> 00:11:07,250
我知道这是一起该死的屠杀
I understand it was a damn slaughter.

163
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:13,480
你想要我帮你查查么?
Would you like me to look into it for you?

164
00:11:14,990 --> 00:11:16,530
滚你妈的
Fuck you.

165
00:11:19,110 --> 00:11:21,260
这是在案发现场门外拍到的
That's outside the house where it happened.

166
00:11:21,260 --> 00:11:24,750
下午2点53分 你是主要嫌疑人
2:53 PM. You're the main suspect.

167
00:11:24,750 --> 00:11:27,320
我真他妈希望他们把你钉死在墙上
I hope they nail your ass to the wall.

168
00:11:38,310 --> 00:11:40,450
- Saul在哪里?
- 在审讯室里
- Where's Saul? - In the interrogation room.

169
00:11:41,280 --> 00:11:43,620
你知道我们要把Javadi送回伊朗吗?
Did you know we're sending Javadi back to Iran?

170
00:11:47,070 --> 00:11:48,280
你错过好戏了
You missed the fireworks.

171
00:11:48,280 --> 00:11:52,060
Javadi听到自己要回去以后魂都吓没了
我们得等到他把血止住
Javadi blew when he found out he had to go back. We're on hold till they stop the bleeding.

172
00:11:52,060 --> 00:11:55,160
- 最好不要等太久
- 该死
We better not wait too long. Shit.

173
00:12:02,910 --> 00:12:04,540
我刚要重新开始 怎么了?
I'm about to start again. What's the deal?

174
00:12:04,540 --> 00:12:07,410
小区里的监控录像拍到我了
警方放出了全境通缉
Neighbor's security camera picked me up. There's an APB out.

175
00:12:08,790 --> 00:12:11,270
- 只是你?
- 是的 不知道为什么没拍到Javadi和Carrie
Just you? Yeah, somehow it missed Javadi and Carrie.

176
00:12:11,270 --> 00:12:13,860
- 从哪儿弄到的?
- Dar Adal 记录是他监视着的
Where'd you get this? Dar Adal. He monitors the blotters.

177
00:12:13,860 --> 00:12:16,920
- 所以他知道Javadi入境了?
- 他知道出事了 但是不知道实情
So he knows Javadi's in the country? He knows something's up; he's not in on it.

178
00:12:16,920 --> 00:12:18,440
我建议你赶快去找他谈谈
I suggest you go talk to him soon.

179
00:12:18,440 --> 00:12:19,690
- 我会的
- 我是说马上
- I will. - I mean now.

180
00:12:19,690 --> 00:12:22,120
- 他很火大
- 我会把事情压下去 与此同时
He's furious. I'll smooth things over. In the meantime,

181
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:25,850
你躲在这里不要出去 我们不能让你被捕
you need to stay out of sight here in this building. We can't risk having you arrested.

182
00:12:25,850 --> 00:12:29,530
- 好吧 但是我们要怎么做?
- Bethesda警局有个队长欠我一个人情
Fine, but what do we do about this? There's a police captain in Bethesda who owes me.

183
00:12:29,530 --> 00:12:32,060
我可以打电话给他 至少让他撤下照片
I could call him, at least get the photo down off the wire.

184
00:12:32,060 --> 00:12:35,100
去吧 去和他面谈 用你国家安全局的身份
Do it, face-to-face. Play the national security card.

185
00:12:35,100 --> 00:12:36,520
告诉他我在背后全力支持你
Tell him you have my full support.

186
00:12:37,160 --> 00:12:39,030
万一他要谋杀的细节怎么办?
What if he wants details about the murder?

187
00:12:40,110 --> 00:12:41,150
不能告诉他
He can't have them.

188
00:12:41,150 --> 00:12:43,900
如果任何人猜到Javadi在境内 我们就完了
If anyone even suspects Javadi's in the country, we're through.

189
00:12:45,190 --> 00:12:46,360
去啊
Well?

190
00:12:46,360 --> 00:12:48,990
我查了整幢房子的监控 我一定是忘了邻居家的
I checked the whole house for surveillance. I must have missed the neighbors.

191
00:12:48,990 --> 00:12:52,450
- 是啊 我他妈整件事情都搞砸了
- 进行得怎样了?
Yeah, well, I missed the whole fucking thing. How's it going in there?

192
00:12:52,450 --> 00:12:53,340
很慢
Slowly.

193
00:13:02,510 --> 00:13:05,160
- 有困难?
- 哦 我们会有办法的
Trouble? Oh, we'll manage.

194
00:13:06,590 --> 00:13:07,760
你看起来很不高兴
You seem upset.

195
00:13:08,480 --> 00:13:09,700
这样就好了
That's good enough.

196
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:24,470
- 嗯?
- 嗯什么?
Well? Well what?

197
00:13:26,610 --> 00:13:28,880
你有没有接受目前的状况?
Have you come to terms with your situation?

198
00:13:30,610 --> 00:13:31,950
怎么进行?
How does it work?

199
00:13:32,730 --> 00:13:35,270
我们尽快把你送回你的国家
We return you to your people as soon as possible.

200
00:13:35,270 --> 00:13:37,610
我假设他们已经给你找好了离开本国的路径
I assume they've arranged a way for you to get out of the country.

201
00:13:37,610 --> 00:13:39,580
不 我是说Fariba
No, I meant about Fariba.

202
00:13:40,880 --> 00:13:43,440
这宗罪行必须得掩饰过去
A crime is committed that must be covered up.

203
00:13:44,810 --> 00:13:46,330
这里的程序是什么?
How does it work here?

204
00:13:48,540 --> 00:13:50,020
你杀了她
You killed her.

205
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:52,390
为什么?
Why?

206
00:13:53,320 --> 00:13:55,560
尽你所能来回击我?
Get back at me because you could?

207
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:02,270
她是我的妻子 她对我不忠
She was my wife. She was unfaithful.

208
00:14:02,270 --> 00:14:05,910
她是你的前妻 都是35年前的事了
She was your ex-wife. It was 35 years ago.

209
00:14:05,910 --> 00:14:08,780
在神看来 我们还是夫妻
In the eyes of God, we're still married.

210
00:14:10,880 --> 00:14:12,950
我应该用石头砸死她
I should have stoned her to death,

211
00:14:12,950 --> 00:14:15,640
但是你给我的时间不够
but you didn't give me enough time.

212
00:14:25,180 --> 00:14:26,180
还记得这个吗?
Remember this?

213
00:14:26,660 --> 00:14:28,530
是Fariba的21岁生日
It was Fariba's 21st birthday.

214
00:14:30,370 --> 00:14:32,830
我们谈了一整晚 我们四个人
We talked all night, the four of us,

215
00:14:33,980 --> 00:14:35,780
谈论未来会带给我们什么
about what the future might bring.

216
00:14:40,460 --> 00:14:41,650
不该是这样的
It wasn't this.

217
00:15:34,630 --> 00:15:35,590
Carrie?
Carrie?

218
00:15:35,590 --> 00:15:39,900
- 不是说到外面去谈么
- 我的人有几个问题
I thought we were meeting outside. My guys have a few questions.

219
00:15:39,900 --> 00:15:41,510
你告诉他们我不能说 对吧?
You told them I can't talk about it, right?

220
00:15:41,510 --> 00:15:43,240
是的 我和他们说了
Yeah, I told them.

221
00:15:44,690 --> 00:15:46,310
Johnson警探
Detectives Johnson,

222
00:15:46,310 --> 00:15:48,890
Cort警探 Carrie Mathison
Cort, Carrie Mathison.

223
00:15:51,620 --> 00:15:54,330
好吧 我知道这样你们不高兴
Okay, I understand you're not happy about this.

224
00:15:54,330 --> 00:15:57,130
- 哦 你高兴么?
- 当然不高兴了
Oh, and you are? Of course not.

225
00:15:57,130 --> 00:15:58,440
我们和你们一样不满
We're as upset as you.

226
00:16:00,420 --> 00:16:03,340
- 这人是谁啊?
- 我恐怕不能说
So who's this guy? I'm afraid that's classified.

227
00:16:03,340 --> 00:16:06,120
- 但是他是你们的人?
- 嗯 这点也不能说
But he's one of yours? Well, that's classified, too.

228
00:16:07,880 --> 00:16:11,920
- 你能告诉我他在这里干什么吗?
- 我不能...
Can you tell me what he was doing here? That's...

229
00:16:11,920 --> 00:16:14,040
你能告诉我他怎么认识受害人的吗?
Can you tell me how he knew the victims?

230
00:16:15,010 --> 00:16:17,270
- 好吧 等下
- 你他妈能告诉我什么啊?
- Okay, wait a second. - Can you tell me any goddamn thing at all?

231
00:16:17,270 --> 00:16:19,920
你能告诉我为什么这位女士会躺在这里
喉咙被人割烂了?
Can you tell me why this lady's laying here with her throat cut to ribbons?

232
00:16:19,920 --> 00:16:21,110
你到底能他妈说什么?
Any fucking thing?

233
00:16:29,340 --> 00:16:30,540
失陪
Excuse me.

234
00:16:31,430 --> 00:16:32,440
好吧 队长?
Okay, Cap?

235
00:16:48,420 --> 00:16:50,830
你不是个狂热分子 你很现实
You're not a fanatic. You're a pragmatist.

236
00:16:51,410 --> 00:16:52,450
一直都是
Always have been.

237
00:16:53,680 --> 00:16:56,030
我是谁不是谁轮不到你来说
Don't tell me what I am and what I am not.

238
00:16:57,280 --> 00:17:00,180
我们都老了 这点没什么可争的吧
Well, we're both old men. There's no disputing that.

239
00:17:02,520 --> 00:17:03,480
的确
We are.

240
00:17:05,070 --> 00:17:09,560
年纪大的诅咒就是你会意识到
最终我们什么也控制不了
It's the curse of old men to realize that in the end, we control nothing.

241
00:17:12,640 --> 00:17:13,880
所以我们要爆发
So we lash out.

242
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:21,150
布宜诺斯艾利斯 柏林
Buenos Aires, Berlin...

243
00:17:22,560 --> 00:17:23,690
卑尔根(挪威城市)
Bergen.

244
00:17:25,120 --> 00:17:27,080
这些都是小打小闹 Majid
These are small acts, Majid.

245
00:17:28,870 --> 00:17:30,310
跟你配不上
Unworthy of you.

246
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:33,160
你漏了一点
You left something out.

247
00:17:34,910 --> 00:17:36,580
CIA爆炸案
The bombing of the CIA.

248
00:17:38,070 --> 00:17:40,040
这可不小
Nothing small about that.

249
00:17:40,040 --> 00:17:44,100
- 这可就配得上了
- 我本来也想和你谈谈那事的
Nothing unworthy. Well, I wanted to talk about that, too.

250
00:17:44,760 --> 00:17:48,410
- 你当然想了
- 因为当爆炸发生以后
I'm sure you do. Because when that bomb went off,

251
00:17:49,040 --> 00:17:50,760
死了那么多的人
killing all those people,

252
00:17:52,090 --> 00:17:53,870
很多是我的朋友
many of them my friends,

253
00:17:56,330 --> 00:17:56,790
我的第一个念头
my first thought

254
00:17:56,790 --> 00:17:58,390
不是复仇
was not revenge.

255
00:17:59,720 --> 00:18:00,780
而是...
It was...

256
00:18:02,250 --> 00:18:04,140
"我们得做出改变"
"Something has to change. "

257
00:18:06,100 --> 00:18:07,910
以牙还牙 以眼还眼
You hit us, we hit you.

258
00:18:08,680 --> 00:18:10,040
总是一成不变
It's always the same.

259
00:18:11,340 --> 00:18:12,280
那么...
And...

260
00:18:13,540 --> 00:18:17,760
我作为你的间谍回国会改变这一切吗?
how does my going back as your spy change any of that?

261
00:18:19,010 --> 00:18:22,880
常年以来 我们在后台辛勤劳作 你和我
For years, we toiled in back rooms, you and I.

262
00:18:23,540 --> 00:18:24,640
我们辛勤劳作
We toiled

263
00:18:25,360 --> 00:18:27,530
让肤浅之辈在舞台上亮相
while shallower men held the stage,

264
00:18:28,810 --> 00:18:30,760
等待我们上台的那一刻
waiting for our time to come,

265
00:18:32,150 --> 00:18:34,560
渐渐意识到那一刻永远不会来
gradually understanding it never would.

266
00:18:34,560 --> 00:18:38,040
突然 这一刻来了
Now it has, unexpectedly.

267
00:18:38,670 --> 00:18:40,030
对你来说 是来了
For you, it has.

268
00:18:43,880 --> 00:18:45,780
你是那个让一切变成可能的人
You're the one who made it possible.

269
00:18:47,160 --> 00:18:48,970
我想要还情
I want to return the favor.

270
00:18:50,690 --> 00:18:52,980
你觉得这像是在还情吗 Saul?
Does this look like a favor to you, Saul?

271
00:18:52,980 --> 00:18:57,690
Majid 多亏了你 我得以站在舞台的正中央
Majid, thanks to you, I stand at the center of things.

272
00:18:58,210 --> 00:18:59,710
我的权力是你赐予的
You put me in power.

273
00:19:00,260 --> 00:19:02,980
你回德黑兰去 我也会为你做同样的事
You go back to Tehran, I'll do the same for you.

274
00:19:04,970 --> 00:19:07,520
我知道一个方法
I know a way.

275
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:15,850
你没事吧?
You all right?

276
00:19:15,850 --> 00:19:17,580
是的 抱歉 我不知道发生了什么事
Yeah, sorry. I don't know what happened there.

277
00:19:18,820 --> 00:19:22,940
- 所以我们说定了?
- 我可不觉得 不行 
So are we okay? I wouldn't say so, no.

278
00:19:22,940 --> 00:19:24,890
抱歉 你不能把这事处理掉吗?
I'm sorry, but can't you handle that?

279
00:19:24,890 --> 00:19:28,170
你是说 我不能以长官身份把这事压下去吗?
You mean, can't I just pull rank and shut this thing down?

280
00:19:28,170 --> 00:19:32,570
当然了 你现在不也正在压我呢吗
但是你知道接下来会怎样吗?
Sure, just like you try with me. But you know what happens next?

281
00:19:32,570 --> 00:19:35,250
那张照片和这房间里的所有证据都会
Somehow that photo and all the evidence in this room

282
00:19:35,250 --> 00:19:38,540
莫名其妙出现在德拉吉报道
甚至该死的维基泄密上面
show up on Drudge Report or goddamn Wikileaks,

283
00:19:38,540 --> 00:19:40,560
到那时你才真是遇上麻烦了
and then you've got yourself a real problem.

284
00:19:41,610 --> 00:19:44,220
别用那种我一点忙也帮不上的眼神看我
And don't look at me like I'm being less than helpful.

285
00:19:44,220 --> 00:19:46,620
我只是告诉你事实而已
I'm just talking reality here.

286
00:19:48,320 --> 00:19:49,720
那你说怎么办?
So what do you suggest?

287
00:19:49,720 --> 00:19:51,840
他们想要和照片里的人谈谈
They want to talk to the guy in the photo.

288
00:19:52,740 --> 00:19:55,480
- 那不可能
- 你想不想悄无声息地解决这事啊?
- That's impossible. - You want this thing closed quietly?

289
00:19:56,390 --> 00:19:57,570
那就想个办法
Find a way.

290
00:20:07,040 --> 00:20:09,050
- Quinn哪儿去了?
- 呃 外面吧 大概
Where's Quinn? Uh, outside, I think.

291
00:20:09,050 --> 00:20:13,270
- 能找到他吗?
- 是不是计划从一开始就是把他送回伊朗?
Could you find him? Was it always the plan to send Javadi back to Iran?

292
00:20:13,270 --> 00:20:15,940
- 希望是如此
- 没人告诉我
It was always the hope. No one told me.

293
00:20:15,940 --> 00:20:18,490
嗯 自豪点吧 这都是你达成的
Well, you should be proud. Your work made it all possible.

294
00:20:18,490 --> 00:20:23,630
我才不自豪 他对这个国家做的事情
比起他对伊朗做的事来简直是九牛一毛
I'm not proud. What he did to this country, it's nothing compared to what he did to Iran.

295
00:20:23,630 --> 00:20:25,110
- 我们应该让他上法庭
- 计划不是那样的
- We should try him for what he's done. - That's not the plan.

296
00:20:25,110 --> 00:20:28,730
计划不是这样的 请帮我找到Quinn
That's not the plan. Go find Quinn, please.

297
00:20:35,470 --> 00:20:36,670
- 他同意了 
- 很好
- He's in. - Good.

298
00:20:36,670 --> 00:20:38,910
- 你那边处理得怎样了?
- 不太好
How'd you make out? Not so well.

299
00:20:40,260 --> 00:20:43,070
当地警察想找你谈谈
They want to talk to you- the local cops do.

300
00:20:43,070 --> 00:20:45,410
- 你告诉他们不可能 对吧?
- 说过好几遍
- You told them that was impossible, right? - Several times.

301
00:20:45,410 --> 00:20:47,040
我还以为你的队长朋友会把这事处理掉
I thought your captain friend was gonna take care of this.

302
00:20:47,040 --> 00:20:48,480
是啊 我本来也希望的 被他耍了
Yeah, me, too. He boned me.

303
00:20:48,480 --> 00:20:51,170
最重要的是不能危害到Javadi计划
The important thing here is to not jeopardize the Javadi play.

304
00:20:51,170 --> 00:20:53,670
对吧? 那我去和当地警察谈谈
Agreed? So let me talk to them, the cops.

305
00:20:53,670 --> 00:20:55,880
- 你要怎么说?
- 我不知道 看他们问什么吧
And say what? I don't know, see what they ask.

306
00:20:55,880 --> 00:20:57,240
你知道他们会怎么问
You know what they'll ask.

307
00:20:57,240 --> 00:21:00,300
你是他们唯一的嫌疑人
既然你不能告诉他们事实是什么
You're their only suspect,
and since you can't tell them what actually happened,

308
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:03,100
你就得承认自己杀了两个人
还不准他们逮捕你
you'll be admitting to two murders
and then saying they can't touch you for it.

309
00:21:03,100 --> 00:21:04,130
好吧
Okay.

310
00:21:04,130 --> 00:21:06,850
听着 警方可能会危及到我们的行动
Look, we have police threatening to blow up our operation.

311
00:21:06,850 --> 00:21:09,870
我们至少也得要争取时间把Javadi弄出国去
At the very least, this buys us enough time to get Javadi out of the country.

312
00:21:09,870 --> 00:21:13,150
除非你还有其他选择 先这么做吧
So unless you got another option? Do it.

313
00:21:13,150 --> 00:21:16,610
- 至少让我和他一起去
- 不 Javadi来这里是和你联系
At least let me go with him. No. Javadi came here to contact you.

314
00:21:16,610 --> 00:21:19,950
只有你才能和他在公众场合出现
我需要你送他回他自己人那里去
You're the only one who can be seen with him. I need you to get him back to his people.

315
00:21:19,950 --> 00:21:21,500
- 什么时候?
- 越快越好
- When? - Soon as possible.

316
00:21:21,500 --> 00:21:23,840
你得在发生其他爆炸案之前把他弄出国去
You got to get him out of the country before anything else blows up,

317
00:21:23,840 --> 00:21:27,230
我要你一直呆在他身边
我们不能再搞砸了 懂吗?
and you need to stay right by his side. We cannot risk another screwup, okay?

318
